First of all, Robert, could you say when and where you were born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3566045\charrsid14902524 Robert:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 I was born on the 3}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\super\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 rd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 
 June, 1936, in Beckenham, in Kent \endash  right on the border of London.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3566045\charrsid14902524 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 
And could you tell me something about your family background?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3566045\charrsid14902524 Robert:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 Right.  Well, 
I thought that I came from a very ordinary family, and it took me quite a long time to realise that I came from a rather un-ordinary family.  For example, until I think I was in my early twenties, I assumed that all mothers and fathers were excellent cook
s, and that they would be good at painting and decorating, which my parents were.  It never occurred to me that other people\rquote 
s fathers might not help them with their algebra homework, or that they were not good at woodwork, electrical work, bricklaying, and so on.  And an interesting point there is that my grandfather \endash  my father\rquote s father \endash 
 had a little workshop in the garden where he made toys and did odds and ends.  My father had a workshop, and he did all the household maintenance and lots of other work, 
including making me a model aeroplane that I could sit in, and it had a propeller driven by a wind-up gramophone motor!  And then I have always had a workshop, and I do all the household maintenance, and a certain amount of carpentry and joinery and I enj
oy that.  And sometimes a little bit of metalwork or whatever.  My son has the most eye-watering workshop in his village in South Tyrol \endash  I mean, with the kind of equipment that you would normally expect to see in a professional place.  So there
\rquote s four generations of workshops running down the male side of my family, and it never occurred to me that people didn\rquote t have workshops, it was just a part of the house.  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3566045\charrsid14902524 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 
Was your grandfather living with you, then?
