t to - one went to an orphanage, one went to some kind of training school, so all the five sisters dispersed, and that was it.  I mean, once the breadwinner was gone, there was no parachute, you just plunged down.  So that was my mother\rquote 
s childhood experience.  It was a very tough one.  You know, she talked about mealtimes, watching to see if any of her sisters would leave anything on their plate, because then she would grab it and eat it!  \tab 
