enated from the place that alcohol had in the culture of the Navy, and also through my contacts in the Iona Community and so on, I encountered a number of people who were chronic alcoholics, and I just thought, \'93I want to just get away from this\'94
.  And also this slight thing, slight nagging feeling, I wasn\rquote t a great drinker, I liked a gin and tonic, but I\rquote d have one, that was enough for me, and I thought, \'93Here I am, stuck on a ship, perhaps I\rquote 
m Officer of the Day in harbour, if something goes wrong, a life is lost, and I would always be thinking, \'93Did that one drink make a difference?\'94  \'93If I hadn\rquote t had that drink, would something \'85\'94
 you know, and a kind of nagging thing, so I thought it was much better just to give it all up.  And there were other reasons as well.  So I was a teetotaller.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
