d done all the things, chasing the girls, getting drunk, all that sort of juvenilia, was out of my system, and at the same time, I\rquote d saved enough money, before I came out of the Navy, 
to fund myself through university.  And then I discovered I was entitled to a Mature Student\rquote s grant from the London County Council.  So I got an LCC grant.  So I never ever had to take a job in the vacation.  I had three years at Hull, what
\rquote s three times 
52 weeks?  You know, a hundred and whatever weeks, of being a full-time student.  So in the vacations I was just in the library, and I read and read and read and read, and it never occurred to me not to be doing this. I remember, I was standing outside a 
class one day, and chatting to friends there, and I made some particular comment, and somebody said, \'93Oh, where did you find that out?\'94  And I said, \'93Well, it was something I was reading on Saturday night\'94
.  And everybody looked at me, they said, \'93Saturday night?  You were reading?\'94  I said, \'93Well, yes\'94
.  Saturday, we did the shopping in the morning, because we had a flat, then the afternoon was reading and really having a good run at writing essays, right through till late in the evening, because you could work late, you didn\rquote 
t have to get up.  And then Sunday was more reading.  And this absolutely shocked my peers!  They presumably went out to dances and pubs and things.  But, you know, I had no interest in that.
