 there was quite a big Irish settlement there \endash  and I wouldn\rquote t call it a riot, but there were lots of people out on the street, a
nd they were punching one another, and bricks and bottles were flying around. I heard this was going on, so I dashed down and was immediately stopped by a policeman who said, \'93Oh, you can\rquote t go down there\'94
, and I think I said this in the account, I thought, \'93I\rquote m going to have to get through here somewhere\'94
. So I took my jacket off, and turned it inside out, so I looked different, and had another go, and I got through the police cordon this time, and went and watched what was the end of this fracas, and I fin
ished up hiding under a hedge with bottles and bricks flying over!  Yeah, all in the life of a young sociologist!  And again, I wonder, if I\rquote d not actually been into battle, if I\rquote 
