 and this issue came up in the conference we had yesterday about how you get involved.  I had a girlfriend, who was actually on the point of becoming an ex-girlfriend, but anyhow, I needed somebody to find out exactly what was goi
ng on inside the Conservative Party in Sparkbrook.  And I had this girlfriend who had a very upper class bearing, and she was very nicely-spoken, very kind of nice-looking, she could pass for upper class, so I asked her, she was looking for a bit of part-
time work, and I said, \'93Well, look, if I pay you for a couple of weeks work, would you volunteer to work for the Conservative Party in the General Election campaign?\'94 It was the first Wilson election, would that be \rquote 64, or \rquote 
65?  So she said, \'93Okay, I\rquote ll do that\'94
.  So she went and worked in the Conservative Party offices in Sparkbrook, during the campaign for the General Election.  But while she was there, the Conservative Party fell apart temporarily, because the Tory candidate was a very nice young Bow Grou
p kind of trendy young Tory, who was really very unprepared to have any truck with racism.  The local Tory Party wanted }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14112971\charrsid14902524 
to go the whole hog, you know, \lquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 If you want a nigger }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14112971\charrsid14902524 for a neighbour, vote Labour\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 
