.  And there was a big falling out in the Tory Party, as a result of which, their campaign stopped.  So this girl phoned me up and said, \'93Look, everything\rquote s come to a grinding halt.  What do I do?  Because at the moment, I\rquote 
m keeping the Conservative Party office running\'94.  And I thought, \'93Well, this is a very tricky one.\'94 Because I could actually completely destroy the Conservative Party organisation!  And I said, \'93Well, you know, we\rquote re in there\'94
, I said, \'93and they have taken you on in good faith.  I think you should carry on working\'94.  And she did.  And she kept the thing running for three or four days, and then the Conservative Party sorted itself out and accepted the candidate\rquote 
s position that they weren\rquote t going to distribute racist leaflets, and, you know, life got back to normal in the Tory Party.  But for three or four days it was my research assistant who was 
