Gosh!  Well, there was a woman in Braithwaite Road, in the middle of the minority settlement, who was constantly writing racist letters to the local paper, and so I went to see her, and got on quite friendly terms with her.  I mean, she wasn\rquote 
t a wicked woman, she was very misguided!  (LAUGHS)  So I chatted to her, and got to meet one or two of her friends.  I got to know the local vicar, because he was involved with the c
ommunity, with the Sparkbrook Association; and the doctor, Dr. Barrow, who had lots of friends.  I got to know people by meeting them on the streets, and there was an adventure playground \endash  I think it was one of the first in Britain, in Sparkbrook 
