\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524  alive again.  It was real to him.  He was conjuring those people up again, an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid9966519\charrsid14902524 d it was really upsetting him.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 I had a similar experience with a key 
\endash  as in all these things, you have a key informant \endash 
 and my key informant lived in the village of Cornsay Colliery.  He was a very nice old man, very conservative Methodist, and I think, politically, very Conservative.  But I liked him very much.... So I went to see him one day, and he wasn\rquote 
t at all well, and he received a visit from a friend, who was a lady of the same age, and I just sat there, and I hope I became invisible, and these two just chatted.  They\rquote d known one another probably for 65/70 years, they\rquote 
d been at school toget
her in the village, and they had long-deceased brothers, sisters, uncles, aunts, who knew one another, and as they sat there talking, I could suddenly see, perhaps this is fantasy on my part, but it was almost as if I could see that whole community being 
brought to life again as they talked.  And it was almost as if they, in their reminiscences, were living back in that community.  In that lovely exchange they were re-creating the community of their youth, and I was a very privileged onlooker.  I don
\rquote t think I said anything.  They just talked, very quietly, and some of the silences were very important, because there were clearly things they didn\rquote 
t need to say, because they understood one another.  And it was really lovely!  And this old chap died not all that long after.  But this re-creation of something.  Now, maybe there was an element of fantasy, creating a golden past that didn\rquote 
t really exist, but nevertheless, there was something there that seemed, to me, very concrete.  So events like that, just sitting in on that, what became really quite a private conversation between two very elderly people, was very memorable for me.

