Yeah.  Well, Tom was a local schoolteacher.  I can\rquote t remember if he became a headmaster or not.  His father had blacklegged in the General Strike, and I met people who, in the village, when you mentioned his name, they spat.  Now, this was over 40 
years after the event.  I know an old man who, whenever a blackleg died, he used to go down to the pub and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid8460833\charrsid14902524 buy himself a whisky and drink 
