ns to be Methodist Ministers, but in the twenties and thirties, public administration was beginning to open up a bit \endash 
 Local Government and so on - so you find quite a few of their sons going to grammar school, and then going into Local Government jobs, or
 minor Civil Service jobs, and in a few cases going to university, and usually becoming schoolteachers.  Now, Tom Greener was one of these.  
