\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid3566045\charrsid14902524 Robert:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 
I wish I knew!  I just find any kind of fieldwork just starts me thinking theoretically, and once I start sitting back at base reading theory books, I want to get back in the field!  I say, \'93Is it really like this on the ground for real people?\'94
  How does this relate to life?  And so perhaps I finish up contributing to neither, I don\rquote t know!  (LAUGHS)  I just feel sorry 
for people that spend all their time as very academic sociologists who are just in the library writing about theory and meta-theory, and theories of theory, and so on.  The real excitement of sociology, and it\rquote 
s theoretical, may be in reading the print-out
 from your logistic regression, or it may be out there talking to people, or it may be out there on the street while people are fighting all around you, or it might be singing in the church on Sunday, or engaging in intense theological debate with a very 
pious Muslim, which I\rquote ve done.  People like talking about religion, you know.  Those are the exciting things for a sociologist, I think.  I love si}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid11959815\charrsid14902524 tting in the library, and I\rquote ve }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid7999863\charrsid14902524 
loved, all my life, reading, but I also want to get out there and do things.  Anyhow, we\rquote re only just beginning my career in Aberdeen!
