mic culture and history, and its enormous contribution to Western civilisation.  At times I\rquote m almost tempted to say \'93its civilisation of the West\'94
. Whenever people start making comments about Islam and the West, I point out that it was Muslims who taught We
sterners to wash.  That greatly amuses my Muslim friends who agree!  But I just find having done that, and appreciated the extent of the contribution to Western culture and science, I mean, I\rquote 
m not an academic who is an expert in Islamic contribution to Western culture, I am a dabbler who happens to be a sociologist, who makes sense of that data in which I\rquote ve dabbled, in sociological ways.  So I\rquote 
d always meant to read up on the Crusades \'85
